  • What’s included in the GRSICO Home Security System 15 piece?

    The GRSICO Home Security System starter kit includes a Base Station, eight entry sensors, two motion sensors, two remote fobs and two keypads to arm and disarm the system.

  • How does the security system work?

    When a sensor is triggered in arm mode, at this time the sensor reports the SOS status to the Base Station, triggering an alarm.

  • How to Reset the Base Station?

    1. Turn OFF the Base Station.

    2. Press and hold the SET button, and turn ON the Base Station while pressing the SET button.

    3. You will hear 2 beeping sounds. Now the Base Station has been RESET.

  • What if my sensor will not connect, or the hub will not alarm when I trigger the sensor?

    1. Installation: The convex triangular sides of the sensor and magnet need to face each other.

    2. Battery: If the sensor LED flashes quickly, it is working.

    3.Signal Range: Try to move the Sensor closer to the Base Station.

  • If the Base Station always alarm, what should I do?

    Reset the Base Station, then pair again.

    Easy to set up. Several pages of instructions that are easy to follow. The Smart Home app is required for set up, but the fobs, keypad, or even Alexa can handle the day to day alarm on and off. I have it set to come on at night and turn off in the morning so I don't even need the fob.

I almost said it did not come with double sided tape for the sensors, but I found the tape in it's own compartment in the well padded box. This alarm works great with my existing Fuers W1 sensors. The W1 fobs work, but the buttons are rearranged. There are several alarm sounds to choose from so you can certainly find one that will wake you up or alert neighbors.

  • Happy shopper
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    GRSICO 15 piece home alarm system review.
    Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2024
    Color: B-15Pack
    System was relatively simple to set up and connect to Wifi via Bluetooth from a smartphone and Smart Life App. Just a matter of assigning sensors to the system and then mounting them in place. Monitoring the system status and being able to arm and disarm via... See more
    System was relatively simple to set up and connect to Wifi via Bluetooth from a smartphone and Smart Life App.
    Just a matter of assigning sensors to the system and then mounting them in place.

    Monitoring the system status and being able to arm and disarm via smartphone, even when away from home is a plus.

    2 key fobs and 2 keypads are included in the 15 piece system as an alternative to arming and disarming via smartphone.

    I opted to pay for phone and message alerts for alarm events.

    You can go into the Smart Life app and turn on and off notifications so that if you are testing the system by triggering the alarm, it won't send notifications if you shut notifications off. You can turn notifications back on as you please.

    One concern that I have is regarding ongoing availability of additional accessories.

    After setting up the system, I decided that I wanted to order two additional key fobs.

    I go onto Amazon to order the key fobs and get the message "Item currently unavailable. We don't know when or if item will be back in stock" which does not sound very encouraging. There is another alarm system sold on Amazon called "Tolviviov" and the sensors, keypads and fobs look identical to the GRSICO ones and the Fobs are currently available for them.

    I will order one fob for the Tolviviov system to try out to see if it works or not with the GRSICO system and will order more from Tolviviov if it does work.

    *Followup edit*. I received the Key fob for the Tolviviov Home Alarm system and tried it out.....It linked right up to my GRSICO system and works fine....so that is an option for those looking for additional key fobs for the GRSICO home alarm system.

    Didn't have high expectations but I thought it would work. I've installed a few professional systems. I realize there's not much to it. First off The sensor on my back door falls off all the time. Can't figure out why. So I had to use this classy looking piece of tape. Only reason I bought it was because it made it sound like it would notify me through the app of an alarm. That's all I need, but no such luck.
